# Open debugfs on the test image\nsudo debugfs -w test.img\n\n# Example command to corrupt the inode of 'file1'\ndebugfs:  modify_inode <inode_number> (where <inode_number> is the inode number of /data/file1)\n\n# Example command to corrupt a block\ndebugfs:  write_block <block_number> <data> (where <block_number> is a specific block you want to corrupt)\n\n# Close debugfs\ndebugfs:  quit